Mouthparts regular. Upper lip rounded below. Lower lip regular, inner lobes small, well developed. Mandible, raker setae row with numerous blades (8–14); lacinia 4–5-dentate; palp segment 3 usually longer than 2; segment 1 short, with acute medial process. Maxilla 1, inner plate triangular, tip not attenuated, inner margin with numerous setae; outer plate with 9 apical tooth setae (Watling type 
III.1
) (
Watling 1989
); palp segment 1 usually with strong lateral setae or without setae. Maxilla 2, inner plate, inner face with oblique or distally submarginal row of numerous setae. Maxilliped, outer plate medium large; palp segment 2 columnar; dactylus medium.
